title: The works of Professor Wilson of the University of Edinburgh,
author: Wilson, John
snippet: I left Altrive after breakfast — about nine — and the Douglas Burn lookin gey temptin, I tried it wi' the black gnat, and sune creeled some fowre or five dizzen — the maist o' them sma' — few exceedin a pund.
